Description: Jackson’s Pro Series Dinky™ models provide the ultimate shred experience. The Pro Series DK2QM features an alder body with a striking quilt maple cap, flat-sawn graphite-reinforced bolt-on maple neck with wrap-around heel, rolled fingerboard edges and heel-mount truss rod adjustment wheel. Its bound 12"-16" compound-radius maple fingerboard hosts 24 jumbo frets and offset black dot inlays. This formidable metal machine is powered by the popular Seymour Duncan (JB TB-4/’59 SH-1N) humbucking pickups with five-way blade switching and single volume and tone controls. The DK2QM is also equipped with a Floyd Rose tremolo bridge system, Dunlop dual-locking Straplok retainers, black and chrome hardware and a pointed 6-in-line headstock that matches the elegant Chlorine Burst finish. This guitar is in excellent condition! It has no major scratches or chips to the body, it does have a different Floyd rose bridge compared to similar models (see pictures). This guitar does not come with any manuals or paper work. The original Jackson hard case is included!
